A complete record of a data upload refers to all the details of the upload including the uploader's information, the data's version information, and the validation status.; 
A validation summary typically includes the total number of rules applied, the number of valid rules, and the number of invalid rules.; 
An access pattern refers to the total number of times a data upload has been accessed, including the number of downloads and views.

